image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Christmas Tree Lighting & Musical Light Show
image:image.image:caption: 6:00PM debut & 8:30PM encore Marana’s beloved annual tradition continues this year with a brand NEW 45ft tree featuring 100,000 RGB lights and new musical playlist synchronized to over 100,000 lights in our landscape trees for a 13 minute show!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Photos with Santa & Mrs. Claus
image:image.image:caption: All ages are encouraged to get their free photo with Santa & Mrs. Claus at the event. Professional photos will be published the week after the event on Marana Parks & Recreation’s Facebook page.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Community Performances
image:image.image:caption: The Candy Cane Stage and Santa’s Courtyard Stage are programmed on the half hour from 3-8PM (except for a break at 6PM for the Tree Lighting)

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Make Memories in Marana
image:image.image:caption: There are so many places in the event to take photos but make sure you stop by the photo set on Marana Main Street near the Town’s booth!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Food Vendors
image:image.image:caption: No festival is complete without an awesome selection of food trucks and food vendors! From Sonoran Hot Dogs, Pizza, Tacos, Burgers and BBQ to Coffee, Hot Cocoa, Snacks, Churros and Fry Bread, Marana events have something for everyone!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Creation Station
image:image.image:caption: Lucky Cat Social Art is happy to present the children’s craft station in Santa’s Courtyard.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Mistletoe Market
image:image.image:caption: The Mistletoe Market features over 35 local Artisans & Craft Vendors offering great products that make great Holiday gifts! You can also talk to Exhibitors, Non-Profits and Town of Marana department’s and organizations! #SHOPLOCAL

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Free Rides on the Holiday Train
image:image.image:caption: Located in Santa’s Courtyard, families can enjoy unlimited, free rides on the Holiday Train at the Marana Train Depot.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Musical Instrument Petting Zoo
image:image.image:caption: The Civic Orchestra of Tucson’s Musical Instrument Petting Zoo provides hands-on opportunities to touch, feel, and play with String and Percussion instruments!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Holiday Festival & Christmas Tree Lighting - Marana Food Bank
image:image.image:caption: It’s the season of giving! Attendees are encouraged to bring (1) can of food or (1) non-perishable food item to donate to the Marana Food Bank. You will find donation stations at each event entrance and at the Marana Food Bank’s booth located in Santa’s Courtyard near the Free Photos with Santa! Learn more.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - MOVIES IN MARANA
image:image.image:caption: LOCATION IN EVENT: In the Pole Barn in the Family Fun Fiesta Zone TIME: 5:45PM at sundown. The last Movies in Marana of the 2024 season will be shown at Fall Festival. The movie is Disney’s 2023 “Haunted Mansion”. Learn more about the Movies in Marana series HERE.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - Beer Garden
image:image.image:caption: PRESENTED BY MARANA HERITAGE CONSERVANCY $5.00 (cash) per beer. This feature is for guests 21 & Up only. ID is required and will be checked by staff. This attraction is located in the Display Garden.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - MUTTON BUSTIN’ CONTEST
image:image.image:caption: PRESENTED BY COWBOYS AND COWGIRLS BARREL RACING ASSOCIATION. SPONSORED BY BAYER U.S. CROP SCIENCE AND FREEDOM RV Registration opens 08/15/2024 *Register Your 4 Year Old HERE *Register Your 5 Year Old HERE *Register Your 6 Year Old HERE *Note: 6 year-olds report to the Corral FIRST at 5:15PM. 5 year-olds report at 5:40PM and 4 year-olds report at 6:10PM.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - Pick Your Own Sunflowers
image:image.image:caption: Marana is famous for its sunflowers on our back country roads and they grow in abundance at Heritage River Park! When the sun goes down, guests can trim a stem off and take a sunflower souvenir of their own.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - Nine Carnival Rides
image:image.image:caption: There are thrills for all ages at our mini-carnival. This year, guests can enjoy the EuroWheel, Vertigo, Zero Gravity, Fun Slide, Speedway, Carousel, Dizzy Dragons, Farm Train and new this year, the Wacky Shack. Tickets are $1 - 1 ticket per ride.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - PUMPKIN CARVING & SPOOKY GARDEN WALK
image:image.image:caption: PRESENTED BY MARANA PARKS & RECREATION’S NATURAL RESOURCE TEAM 2:00 - 5:30PM - Guests can select and pick-out a pumpkin to carve that will be used in the Spooky Garden Walk. Come pick it up at the end of the night! 5:30 - 9:00PM - Guests can enjoy a spooky (not scary) walk through the lit path of the Marana Community Garden featuring seasonal decorations and a Gypsy Fortune Teller!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Star-Spangled Spectacular - CAR SHOW
image:image.image:caption: Presented by Obsessions Car Club Enjoy the 40+ cars right in the middle of the festivities on the southside parking lot near the basketball court. Meeting new people and connecting with old friends is what Obsessions Car Club loves most about doing events.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Star-Spangled Spectacular - SCOTTY FREEL & THE FLYING DIAMONDS (4:30 - 6:15PM)
image:image.image:caption: For nearly five years, Scotty Freel & the Flying Diamonds have been considered to be the house band at popular Marana restaurant, Lil’ Abner’s and also regularly play nights The Maverick and Whiskey Roads. Scotty shares some of the lead vocal duties with young lead guitar 'Diamond,' Jake Weller, son of the bass player, Gavin. Randy Cheatham keeps the beat on the drums. They have one of the most diverse country playlists you'll hear anywhere, with songs from Morgan Wallen, Chris Stapleton, Jon Pardi and Blake Shelton, ranging all the way to Strait, Cash, and Haggard. You could also by hear Justin Timberlake music, Ed Sheeran, Dire Straits, or Brian Setzer and Michael Bublé. They have strong vocal harmonies, high energy and just a love for playing for a crowd.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Founders' Day - Parade & Festivities - 2024 GRAND MARSHALS: Marana Little League Junior Softball All-Star Team
image:image.image:caption: The Juniors Softball All-Star team from Marana Little League won the West Regional in July of last year becoming the first team (softball or baseball) from the Town of Marana to advance to a Little League World Series. The Juniors Softball World Series was held in Kirkland, Washington, near Seattle. This special group had the opportunity to play teams from around the world (Philippines, Czech Republic, Mexico, and Canada) and the United States (Connecticut (EAST) and Texas (SOUTHWEST)). It was an honor for the girls to represent the Western United States and especially our very own hometown of Marana, AZ!!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Founders' Day - Parade & Festivities - 2024 PARADE JUDGES
image:image.image:caption: 2024 Judging Panel includes: Chief Pridgett of Marana Police Department, Erik Montague, Deputy Town of Marana Manager; and Denelle Veselik, KGUN9 Anchor/Multimedia Journalist. The Judging Station is located on the east side of the intersection of Marana Main Street/Bill Gaudette. Photo shows our 2023 panel of Terry Rozema, Marana’s Town Manager; Amanda Wiggins, President/CEO of the Marana Chamber of Commerce; and Mark Goligoski, Assistant Superintendent of Marana Unified School District.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Founders' Day - Parade & Festivities - COPPER CAFE OPEN FOR BREAKFAST
image:image.image:caption: MHC Healthcare’s Copper Cafe will be OPEN again before the parade from 8-10AM for guests coming to line up on Marana Main Street. MHC Healthcare’s Copper Cafe is located on the first floor of Marana Main Health Center facing Marana Main Street. Breakfast Menu will include: Sausage, Egg & Cheese Biscuit; Ham, Egg & Cheese Burrito, Bacon and Egg Bagel Sandwich, Assorted Muffins, Coffee, and Canned/Bottled Beverages. #SupportLocal and MHC Healthcare on Founders’ Day!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Founders' Day - Parade & Festivities - The Maguire Academy of Irish Dance (11:30 AM)
image:image.image:caption: The Maguire Academy of Irish Dance is located in Tucson and teaches dancers the art of traditional Irish dance. The school is owned and instructed by Darren Maguire, who was the lead dancer in Riverdance for 14 years. We offer classes from the ages of 2.5 up to adults. We compete locally, regionally, nationally and at the world championships every year! You can find us online at maguireacademy.com.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Founders' Day - Parade & Festivities - Traditional Chinese Lion Dance (1:30PM)
image:image.image:caption: Performing in the Marana Police Department Plaza! To honor the substantial Chinese community that developed in the Marana area in the 1880s, the Tucson Chinese Cultural Center returns to perform a traditional Lion Dance at the event and encouraged guests to touch the colorful lion costumes for “good luck.” Learn more about the Tucson Chinese Cultural Center HERE.

image:image.image:caption: We are the Sundowners 4-H Club. The 4-H motto is "To Make the Best Better" and that is what we strive for. We are a small club with great families and try to have a lot of fun. We offer projects for kids ranging in ages of 6-18 years old. The projects we offer are Cloverbuds (6-8 year olds), (8-18year olds) Poultry, Dairy Goat, Rabbit, Market and Breeding Lamb, Market, Breeding and Carcus Swine, Archery, Air Rifle, Small Bore rifle, Photography and Woodworking. image:image.image:title: Calendar - Town of Marana Presents: Fall Festival - Scotty Freel and the Flying Diamonds (4PM-9PM)
image:image.image:caption: Playing in the DISPLAY & BEER GARDEN. For nearly five years, Scotty Freel & the Flying Diamonds have been considered to be the house band at popular Marana restaurant, Lil’ Abner’s and also regularly play nights The Maverick and Whiskey Roads. Scotty shares some of the lead vocal duties with young lead guitar 'Diamond,' Jake Weller, son of the bass player, Gavin. Randy Cheatham keeps the beat on the drums. They have one of the most diverse country playlists you'll hear anywhere, with songs from Morgan Wallen, Chris Stapleton, Jon Pardi and Blake Shelton, ranging all the way to Strait, Cash, and Haggard. You could also by hear Justin Timberlake music, Ed Sheeran, Dire Straits, or Brian Setzer and Michael Bublé. They have strong vocal harmonies, high energy and just a love for playing for a crowd.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Danzacultura Mexicana at 3PM
image:image.image:caption: PERFORMING on the Display Garden Stage. Danzacultura Mexicana was founded in Tucson, Arizona in 1997 and is a 501(c)(3) organization. They are dedicated to keeping the knowledge of Mexican culture alive through the arts of dance, sewing, crafts and Mexican history. Learn More

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Creation Station
image:image.image:caption: New This Year - Lucky Cat Social Art will be helping kids craft leather tassel keychains and punched leather keychains. There is a long tradition of leather crafting in Mexico and these tassels are very colorful leathers: festive and bright for the Hispanic Heritage Month!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Ultimate Tot Zone
image:image.image:caption: New This Year - For ages 0 to 5 only: The Ultimate Tot Zone is the perfect soft play zone for your littles. It is 20ft x 20ft (400sqft) in size and includes Soft play climbers, Soft play Blocks, Basketball hoop, Roller Coaster, Bounce House, Rocking Horse, 8 Animal Hoppers, Ball Pit w/ Slide, Climbing Caterpillar and Legos.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - ROH Band performs 5-9PM
image:image.image:caption: PERFORMING on the Display Garden Stage. ROH Band has been bringing a wide variety of live music to Tucson for the last sixteen years. Well known for their male / female vocal energy that brings to life popular hits in the genres of Classic Rock, Rock, R & B, Blues, Funk, Love Songs, Standards, Swing, Originals, and more. They magically bridge the generation gaps with their high-energy, emotive performances that will have you dancing the night away. If you haven’t experienced ROH Band, now’s the time! Learn More.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Mutton Bustin’
image:image.image:caption: PRESENTED BY FREEDOM RV Click on the link below to Pre-Register your 4-6 year old child. No cost to register but $20 cash day-of-event per child! Register Your 4 Year Old Register Your 5 Year Olds Register Your 6 Year Olds

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Alpaca Meet & Greet
image:image.image:caption: New This Year - Presented by Double G Alpacas, they specialize in Huacaya alpacas and are located just outside Sierra Vista, AZ in the middle of the San Pedro Valley. At the event, come say howdy and learn about the adorable alpacas. Guests can then peruse Double craft G’s tent for handmade items made from alpaca wool.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Ballet Folklorico La Paloma at 2PM
image:image.image:caption: Ballet Folkorico La Paloma is a non-profit organization dedicated to perpetuating the native folk dances of Mexico. By doing so, we hope to arouse pride and heritage in the Mexican- American community.We also educate the general public through our colorful and entertaining performances. Ballet Folklorico La Paloma has responded to the need of positive and responsive programs for young people in our community since 1982. Through the reinvestment of time, funds, and energy we have been able to help develop positive, and committed young people who will make a better future for generations to come. Learn More.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Sunflower Field
image:image.image:caption: Marana is famous for its sunflowers on our back country roads and they grow in abundance at Heritage River Park! When the sun goes down, guests can break a stem and take a sunflower souvenir of their own.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Carnival Rides
image:image.image:caption: There are thrills for all ages at our mini-carnival. Guests can enjoy the EuroWheel, Vertigo, Zero Gravity, Dizzy Dragons, Speedway, and Farm Train. Tickets are $1 - 1 ticket per ride.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Wednesday Morning Trio 2:30PM, 3:30PM, 4:30PM
image:image.image:caption: PERFORMING on the Fiesta Stage. This fun group primarily plays country and folk, but they’ll be bringing their best kids music for short 20 minute sets along with some classics for the whole family to sing and dance along to. The trio is made up entirely of multi-instrumentalists; between the three of them, they can cover about ten different instruments. Oliver Dewey and Wednesday Aparisi both teach private music lessons, and Tim O’Connor gigs all over Tucson and surrounding areas and has since the 70’s!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Dog Adoptions
image:image.image:caption: SPONSORED BY RENEWAL BY ANDERSEN Marana Community Services & HSSA present dog adoptions at Fall Festival. All dogs at the event have had their fees covered by Renewal by Andersen. Fall in love with a new pet at Fall Festival and go home with a new dog!(Note: Dog pictured here is from a past event and for promo use only).

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana Fall Festival - Statue Unveiling at 4PM
image:image.image:caption: Marana’s iconic “Man on Horse” statue has been moved to its new home at Heritage Farm Park and will be officially unveiled at 4PM at the festival.

image:image.image:caption: The Town of Marana’s fireworks show is always the finale of a fantastic festival day!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - Jesse Colt Band
image:image.image:caption: Country with a Twist! The Jesse Colt Band is Tucson's newest, upcoming country band. Bringing all the lights and sounds of stadium style concerts directly to you. The Jesse Colt Band brings you all the sounds of your favorite country hits. From Marty Robbins to George Strait with a little Sonoran and Rock thrown in!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - Courtesy Shuttle
image:image.image:caption: This year, the Town of Marana will provide a courtesy shuttle for handicapped guests with a handicap placard or license. The designated lot to park at for the shuttle is at Coyote Trail Elementary School (8000 N Silverbell Rd, Tucson, AZ 85743). The first shuttle will depart at 4:30 PM from the school and the last shuttle will depart the park at 10:30 PM.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - Splash Pad
image:image.image:caption: The Splash Pad at Crossroads Park will be open from 4-8PM during the event.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - Car Show
image:image.image:caption: Enjoy the 40+ cars presented by Obsessions Car Club right in the middle of the festivities! Meeting new people and connecting with old friends is what they love most about doing events.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - OnesAll
image:image.image:caption: OnesAll is a fun funk/rock band from Tucson, AZ. The band features a family of musicians and fuses thick funky grooves, tight vocals, and exciting rock sounds with high-energy performances.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - Musica Instrument Petting Zoo
image:image.image:caption: The Civic Orchestra of Tucson’s Musical Instrument Petting Zoo provides hands-on opportunities to touch, feel, and play with String and Percussion instruments!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Star-Spangled Spectacular in Marana - 30+ Food Trucks
image:image.image:caption: With over 30 vendors on site, you will have a diverse selection to choose from for your full meal, snacks, desserts and beverage needs. The Town of Marana is proud to support small, local businesses at our events. Full list of vendors is TBA.

image:image.image:caption: 11:30AM-1:30PM: GOOD TROUBLE (Classic Rock) 1:30-2:00PM: TUCSON CHINESE CULTURAL CENTER (Lion Dance) 2:00-4:00PM: FREDDY PARISH BAND (Country, Old Time, Bluegrass)

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Historic Marana Exhibits
image:image.image:caption: Stop by the Marana Community Center’s Crafting for a Cause booth to enjoy a Historic Marana Craft Wall and other exhibits throughout the event courtyard.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Corn Hole Tournament & Games
image:image.image:caption: REGISTER EARLY HERE Enjoy friendly family fun and games! Enter the Founders’ Day Corn Hole Tournament for a chance to win prizes, play lawn games, and try your luck at FC Tucson’s soccer inflatable and Tucson Roadrunner’s hockey inflatable!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Bouncy Fun & Games
image:image.image:caption: The Family Fun Zone features inflatables like bouncing castles, obstacle courses and attractions for all ages!

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Car Show
image:image.image:caption: PRESENTED BY OBSESSIONS CAR CLUB Obsessions Car Club started as a way for friends to get together in a casual car-loving environment without the exclusivity and requirements of other car clubs. They have grown significantly since that time, but still live by those values. Meeting new people and connecting with old friends is what they love most about their events.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - 20 Food Trucks
image:image.image:caption: There are dining option for everyone! Featuring: Al Gusto Coffee Co, DC Jumbie Latin Caribbean Food Truck, Fork N Fire, Greater Faith Intl. Church (BBQ), Haus of Brats, Heavy Kettle Corn, Jackie’s Food Court, Just Churros, Marana Heritage Conservancy, Meatball Madness, Ricuras de Venezuela, Ry’s Snacks, Romero’s Sonoran Hotdogs, Smokin’ Monster BBQ, Sweet Sensations Ice Cream & Candy, Tucson Kona Ice, Tuxson Tacos & Sunset Sammies and Soups, & West Coast Trolley.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - PARADE GRAND MARSHAL
image:image.image:caption: PARADE GRAND MARSHALL Jennifer North Morris, Marana High School Mathematics Teacher and Nominee for Arizona Teacher of the Year

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - PARADE
image:image.image:caption: The parade theme this year is “My Favorite Things (About Marana)”! Make sure you line up early on Marana Main Street and surrounding vicinity to get a great spot to see the fantastic parade entries! Best spots will be along Marana Main Street and along W. Civic Center Drive. Want to be in the parade? Sign Up HERE CHECK OUT THE PARADE ROUTE HERE

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Artisan Market & Exhibitors
image:image.image:caption: Support over 30 local small businesses and buy art, crafts, goods and wares from our Artisan Market vendors and Exhibitors.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Creation Station
image:image.image:caption: PRESENTED BY LUCKY CAT SOCIAL ART Free Interactive Learning & Arts Activities! Kids can create a craft on site at the event to take home.

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Celebrate Marana with us!
image:image.image:caption: Enjoy the PARADE 10AM-12PM FESTIVITIES FROM 12PM-4PM include: —CAR SHOW presented by Obsessions Car Club —MUSICAL & DANCE PERFORMANCES —20 FOOD TRUCKS —ARTISAN VENDORS & EXHIBITORS —CREATION STATION presented by Lucky Cat Social Art —CHALK ART ALLEY —INFLATABLES & MORE

image:image.image:title: Calendar - Marana's 45th Anniversary Founders' Day - Chalk Art Alley

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: COMMUNITY AND AQUATIC CENTER TAKING SHAPE Great views of what’s to come for Marana. Construction has been booming as site preparation shapes into walls, courts, pools, and parking lots.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Fitness Rooms Crews have poured even more concrete, but this time for the second-story fitness rooms. The second story will feature two large fitness rooms geared at offering a variety of group fitness classes.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: CONCRETE SMOOTH AS GLASS The foundation for the center’s three gym floors took a total of 271 cubic yards of concrete. Hoop, there it is!

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Multipurpose Rooms The future site of the facility’s two multipurpose rooms now has a roof. Each room will be almost 1,000-sqft and be able to serve 50 people each. The program opportunities are endless!

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Comp Pool is Formed Wow! Just look at the amount of shotcrete work that went into forming the future 12 lanes competition pool. She looks almost seaworthy.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Community and Aquatic Center Site Progress All corners of the site are being developed from parking lot to the east gymnasium walls. Can you picture your first visit here next summer?

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: STEEL COLUMNS AND BEAMS With the block almost complete, it is time to frame the facility with steel columns and beams.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Office Space for Staff Parks and Recreation staff are getting excited about their soon to be home. This space will house admin as well as lifesaving staff.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: DUDE, WHERE’S MY CAR? The main parking lot is almost prepared for pavement. In total, the facility will have over 200 parking spaces. Sweet!

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: BRICK BY BRICK Walls go vertical in what is soon to be the future office of Parks and Recreation staff.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Recreation Pool Shotcrete is complete on the recreation pool. Crews will now strip the forms and begin backfilling around the pool. What feature are you most excited about?

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Competition Pool Gutters The overflow gutter system is now installed on the competition/lap pool. This gutter system is ideal for competitive groups and allows the competition pool to be labeled as a “fast pool”.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Beam Signing Town Staff, Town Council, and our trade partners celebrated the amazing progress with a beam signing ceremony. Not impressed? Did we mention these steel workers are over 40ft in the air!

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: COMMUNITY ROOM VIEWS Block is being completed on the community room doors that will lead to the 1,000sqft courtyard.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: SOME SERIOUS PLUMBING Ever wonder what it takes to circulate water on a commercial pool? The recreation pool has its plumbing mapped out and ready to fill with rock.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Don’t Look Down Crews safely defy gravity as they frame the second story fitness rooms.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Curved Steel Crews are starting to install the steel that will serve as the foundation for the second-story track. This track will feature three lanes and equal a tenth of a mile.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: LOCKER ROOMS AND RESTROOMS The first-floor roofing is now in place at what will soon be 2,800sqft of lockers rooms.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: A View of the Front Entrance Great views of the front entrance and Community Room. The steel roofing is sure to provide a beautiful, covered entry.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: COMPETITION POOL PROGRESS Shotcrete on the Competition Pool is now complete. Soon the forms will be removed to reveal the true shape of this amenity.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: COMPETITION POOL REINFORCED WITH REBAR This pool has been excavated, formed, plumbed, filled with rock and lined with rebar. This masterpiece will become the center’s 12 lane competition pool.

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: RECREATION POOL TAKING SHAPE This feature will include a lap pool, therapeutic resistance channel, splash pad, and a zero-edge entry. Who’s ready to cool off Marana?

image:image.image:title: PARKS AND RECREATION-Construction Updates - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Rec Pool Rebar and Forms Rebar is in place on the recreation pool structure. Next up is the two-week process of shotcrete. Progress is going swimmingly.
